# TravelPlan: Munich to Vienna, 5 days, July 10–14 2026

| Day 1 — 2026-07-10 — Arrival and Innere Stadt | Day 2 — 2026-07-11 — Imperial Vienna museums | Day 3 — 2026-07-12 — Belvedere and food culture | Day 4 — 2026-07-13 — Leopoldstadt and Prater | Day 5 — 2026-07-14 — Departure day |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1. Outbound train: Munich Hbf → Wien Hbf** [transport] 08:00–12:30 @ Munich Hbf to Wien Hbf (€46.00) — Budget-conscious rail transfer from Munich to Vienna. Target a direct ÖBB Railjet/DB service when July 2026 tickets open; current official-style guidance indicates about 4 hours, with advance fares from about €19.99 per person each way. Exact train number/timetable should be booked once released. — Links: [link 1](https://www.oebb.at/), [link 2](https://www.bahn.com/) | **1. Breakfast: local bakery/café near Neubau** [meal] 08:30–09:15 @ Neubau / Zieglergasse area, Vienna (€20.00) — Simple Viennese bakery breakfast before the museum day: coffee, pastries, or rolls near the hotel. | **1. Sunday breakfast: Café Museum near Karlsplatz** [meal] 08:30–09:30 @ Café Museum, Operngasse 7, 1010 Vienna (€25.00) — Sunday-safe breakfast option before the Karlsplatz walk. Café Museum is a historic Viennese café near Karlsplatz/Opera; web verification found it open Sundays from about 08:00, while Naschmarkt produce stalls are closed on Sundays. — Links: [link 1](https://www.cafemuseum.at/en/cafe-museum.html), [link 2](https://www.naschmarkt-wien.at/en/naschmarkt-vienna-opening-hours/) | **1. Breakfast: local bakery/café near Neubau** [meal] 08:30–09:15 @ Neubau / Zieglergasse area, Vienna (€20.00) — Simple breakfast near the hotel before heading to Leopoldstadt/Prater. | **1. Breakfast and check-out** [meal] 08:00–09:00 @ Hotel Pension Walzerstadt / Neubau area (€20.00) — Simple breakfast, pack, and check out of Hotel Pension Walzerstadt. — Links: [link 1](https://travelstack.nuitee.link/hotels/lp6586ac75?checkin=2026-07-10&checkout=2026-07-14&rooms=1&adults=2&occupancies=W3siYWR1bHRzIjoyLCJjaGlsZHJlbiI6W119XQ%3D%3D&language=de&currency=EUR) |
| **2. Transfer to Hotel Pension Walzerstadt** [transport] 12:30–13:15 @ Wien Hbf → Hotel Pension Walzerstadt, 1070 Vienna (€0.00) — Take U-Bahn/tram from Wien Hauptbahnhof toward Neubau/Zieglergasse and drop bags at the hotel. Routing tool was unavailable, so timing is a conservative estimate. — Links: [link 1](https://www.wienerlinien.at/web/wl-en) | **2. Walk/transit to Kunsthistorisches Museum** [transport] 09:15–10:00 @ Hotel Pension Walzerstadt → Kunsthistorisches Museum Wien (€0.00) — Travel from Neubau to Maria-Theresien-Platz. This is a central, walkable segment or short tram/U-Bahn ride; exact routing could not be API-verified. — Links: [link 1](https://www.wienerlinien.at/web/wl-en) | **2. Karlsplatz and Stadtpark architecture walk** [leisure] 10:00–12:00 @ Karlsplatz / Stadtpark, Vienna (€0.00) — Free self-guided walk around Karlsplatz, Otto Wagner pavilion exteriors, Secession area, and Stadtpark edges before lunch. This keeps Sunday lower-cost while still museum/architecture themed. — Links: [link 1](https://www.wienmuseum.at/admission) | **2. Transit to Praterstern / Prater** [transport] 09:15–10:00 @ Hotel Pension Walzerstadt → Praterstern / Prater (€0.00) — Use U-Bahn/tram to reach Praterstern, then walk into the Prater. Routing tool unavailable; timing is conservative. — Links: [link 1](https://www.wienerlinien.at/web/wl-en) | **2. Naschmarkt morning food walk** [leisure] 09:30–11:00 @ Naschmarkt, Wienzeile, 1060 Vienna (€20.00) — Final local-food stroll through Naschmarkt. Official market hours found: Monday–Friday 06:00–21:00; food items vary by vendor. — Links: [link 1](https://www.naschmarkt-wien.at/en/naschmarkt-vienna-opening-hours/) |
| **3. Check-in: Hotel Pension Walzerstadt** [lodging] 13:15–14:00 @ Hotel Pension Walzerstadt, Vienna (€384.00) — Suggested accommodation: Hotel Pension Walzerstadt, a budget-friendly 1070/Neubau option with WiFi and strong hotel-search rating. Quoted search result: €96/night for 4 nights. — Links: [link 1](https://travelstack.nuitee.link/hotels/lp6586ac75?checkin=2026-07-10&checkout=2026-07-14&rooms=1&adults=2&occupancies=W3siYWR1bHRzIjoyLCJjaGlsZHJlbiI6W119XQ%3D%3D&language=de&currency=EUR) | **3. Kunsthistorisches Museum Wien** [attraction] 10:00–13:00 @ Maria-Theresien-Platz, 1010 Vienna (€44.00) — Visit Vienna’s major art-history museum: Bruegel, Kunstkammer treasures, imperial collections, and the grand Semper building. July schedule found: daily 10:00–18:00; adult admission about €22 online. — Links: [link 1](https://www.khm.at/), [link 2](https://www.google.com/maps/search/Kunsthistorisches+Museum+Wien) | **3. Lunch: Vollpension Schleifmühlgasse** [meal] 12:15–13:15 @ Schleifmühlgasse 16, 1040 Vienna (€40.00) — Lunch/cake stop at the original Vollpension near Naschmarkt. Sunday availability checked: official-style web result confirms Schleifmühlgasse is open daily including Sundays, 08:00–20:00; reserve ahead for a July Sunday. — Links: [link 1](https://www.vollpension.wien/en/grannys-public-living-room/4th-district/), [link 2](https://www.vollpension.wien/en/reservation/), [link 3](https://www.vollpension.wien/en/faq/) | **3. Prater Hauptallee walk** [leisure] 10:00–12:30 @ Prater Hauptallee, 1020 Vienna (€0.00) — Free walk along the Prater Hauptallee and quieter green edges before lunch, focusing on local leisure culture and city walking. — Links: [link 1](https://www.google.com/maps/search/Prater+Hauptallee+Vienna) | **3. Lunch: Naschmarkt casual stalls** [meal] 11:00–12:00 @ Naschmarkt, 1060 Vienna (€35.00) — Casual final lunch from Naschmarkt stalls or market restaurants before collecting luggage. — Links: [link 1](https://www.naschmarkt-wien.at/en/nas